<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFB6C3D4DFAA9" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFB6C3D4DFAA9" blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFB6C3F0AFB05" bold="true" box="[199,334,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Richard S. Miller (1945–2021), who first identified these specimens as a new genus and species but never described them. Rich worked primarily on 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFC7FFB403A09FB61" box="[1012,1101,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Lycidae</taxonomicName>
but was knowledgeable about a wide range of beetles and other insects, including all other ‘cantharoids’. Rich was a close friend and colleague of MAI and a role model and source of inspiration to VSF.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFAFD3C5EFA41" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFAFD3C5EFA41" blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFAFD3F06FA94" bold="true" box="[199,322,1302,1328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFEC0FAFC3C52FA95" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[331,534,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFEC0FAFC3C52FA95" box="[331,534,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFCE0FAFC3A5EFA95" box="[875,1050,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCE0FAFC3DA5FA95" box="[875,993,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a dorsally unicolorous pronotum and elytra (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD84FAD03C27FAF1" box="[527,611,1339,1365]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) (vs. pronotal disc in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFCD9FAD03DB1FAF1" box="[850,1013,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ballantynae">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCD9FAD03D21FAF1" box="[850,869,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCFAFAD03DB1FAF1" box="[881,1013,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">ballantynae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
yellow), the pronotum not constricted medially (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE8CFAB43F1FFADD" box="[263,347,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
) (vs. constricted in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFDBDFAB43C80FADC" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[566,708,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFDBDFAB43C0DFADD" box="[566,585,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFDDDFAB43C80FADC" box="[598,708,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the last three abdominal segments distinctly yellow (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFAABFAB43BD7FADD" box="[1312,1427,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F, 1I</figureCitation>
) (vs. dark brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFEE1FA683F8FFA39" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[362,459,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lloydi">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFEE1FA683F39FA39" box="[362,381,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFE00FA683F8FFA39" box="[395,459,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">lloydi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or not distinctly yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFD73FA683DC3FA38" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[760,903,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFD73FA683D4FFA39" box="[760,779,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFC92FA683DC3FA38" box="[793,903,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having ventrite 8 posteriorly entire and apically round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFECCFA4C3FDDFA65" box="[327,409,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
) (vs. notched in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFDDDFA4C3CA1FA64" authorityName="Ferreira, Keller &amp; Branham" authorityYear="2020" box="[598,741,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaragozai">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFDDDFA4C3C2DFA65" box="[598,617,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFDFCFA4C3CA1FA64" box="[631,741,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">zaragozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergite VIII posteriorly notched (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFB19FA4C3A9AFA65" box="[1170,1246,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
) (vs. tergite VIII entire in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFF70FA203F27FA40" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[251,355,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF70FA203F4AFA41" box="[251,270,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFE90FA203F27FA40" box="[283,355,1483,1508]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFE12FA203C4DFA41" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[409,521,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hintoni">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFE12FA203C4DFA41" box="[409,521,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C. hintoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFA053B74F8D5" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFA053A8FF8E9" blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFA053F1DF9AC" bold="true" box="[199,345,1518,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Description.</emphasis>
General color dark brown (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD28FA043D4CF9AD" box="[675,776,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
), mandibles, elytral insertions, trochanters, tarsi and last three abdominal segments yellow (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFDA9F9F83CC1F989" box="[546,645,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1C</figureCitation>
). Head as long as wide; posterior 2/3 covered by pronotum (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFABDF9F83BCAF989" box="[1334,1422,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Antennae when extending posteriorly reaching apical third of elytra (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC29F9DC3DBDF9F5" box="[930,1017,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum not constricted medially; anterior angles round; posterior margin bisinuate (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD41F9B03D65F9D1" box="[714,801,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); median longitudinal carina strongly visible throughout (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFF2BF9943EBDF93D" box="[160,249,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Elytra 3.2× length of pronotum, moderately dehiscent, basally subparallel (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFBE7F9943A81F93D" box="[1132,1221,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
), with two weakly developed elytral costae (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE39F9483C4CF919" box="[434,520,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield posteriorly round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC15F9483DB0F919" box="[926,1012,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Abdomenal tergite VIII with distinct median notch (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFEB5F92C3FCEF945" box="[318,394,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
); ventrite 7 shallowly notched posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFCFBF92C3D85F945" box="[880,961,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC46F92C3DB0F945" box="[973,1012,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[151,1435,181,1901]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Lateral habitus of Chespirito species. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Apically notched and bifurcated ventrite 7 in detail. D–E) C. milleri. Scale bars: A–C = 1 mm, D–E = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405136" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405136/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">2D</figureCitation>
); ventrite 8 elongate, fusiform, longer than wide, entire posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE6CF9003C78F8A1" box="[487,572,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with median lobe stout, fusiform, apically round, in ventral view bearing paired strut-like structure, divergent apically (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFCA0F8E43DC6F88D" box="[811,898,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); parameres apically acuminate, acute (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFAB3F8E43BCAF88D" box="[1336,1422,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
), 1/2 shorter than median lobe; phallobase small, longer than wide, posteriorly rounded (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFBEEF8D83AFAF8E9" box="[1125,1214,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CF8BC3B74F8D5" blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" box="[199,1328,1878,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CF8BC3D7CF8D4" bold="true" box="[199,824,1878,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Length (exposed portion of head+pronotum+elytra).</emphasis>
<quantity id="4C9F9B60FFF2FFACFCB4F8BC3DDCF8D5" box="[831,920,1879,1905]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFC28F8BD3A88F8D4" bold="true" box="[931,1228,1878,1904]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Width (across humerus):</emphasis>
<quantity id="4C9F9B60FFF2FFACFB58F8BC3B68F8D5" box="[1235,1324,1879,1905]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CF8913AA7F831" box="[199,1251,1914,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CF8913AA7F831" blockId="2.[151,1437,1050,1941]" box="[199,1251,1914,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CF8913F25F830" bold="true" box="[199,353,1914,1940]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the Huachuca Mountains in southeast 
<collectingRegion id="49A3F867FFF2FFACFC69F8903A7BF831" box="[994,1087,1915,1941]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, 
